Foot and mouth disease virus (infection with), Kazakhstan
---------------------------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 3 Jan 2022
Confirmed: 14 Jan 2022
Reported: 14 Jan 2022
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 17 Jul 2013
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks (1)
Outbreak location: Kiikty village, Shetskiy, Qaraghandy [Karaganda]
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Jan 2022
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Sheep / 40 / 0 / - / - / - / -
Cattle / 25 / 2 / - / - / - / -

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; zoning; surveillance outside containment and or the protection zone

Domestic control measures to be applied: disinfection, stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Republican State Enterprise National Veterinary Reference Center (national laboratory)
Species / Outbreaks / Test / Tested from / Result
Cattle / 1 / Real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 14 Jan 2022 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

